# IAM directory boundary (`lib/auth/`)

## Authority

- **`lib/auth/`** owns the **IAM control plane**: Better Auth configuration, session/step-up guards, audit writers ([`audit.server.ts`](lib/auth/audit.server.ts)), org IAM audit CSV ([`org-audit.server.ts`](lib/auth/org-audit.server.ts), `org-audit-csv.shared.ts`, `org-audit-export-verify.server.ts`), and permission predicates ([`permission.server.ts`](lib/auth/permission.server.ts) — global admin only; ERP RBAC lives in `#features/erp-rbac`).
- **`lib/features/iam-profile/`** owns **signed-in member profile** data and invitation accept/reject actions (relocated from `lib/auth/` — see [`lib/auth/_RELOCATION.md`](lib/auth/_RELOCATION.md)). Import `#features/iam-profile/server` or `#features/iam-profile/client`, not `#lib/auth`, for those concerns. Three-layer rule: `.cursor/rules/iam-profile-directory.mdc`.
- **`app/[locale]/…`** owns **routes and UI only** — do not introduce an `app/iam/*` URL tree for configuration authority.

## Import rules

- **Public server door:** `#lib/auth` → [`lib/auth/index.ts`](lib/auth/index.ts). Import `auth`, `requireRecentAuthStepUp`, and **all session/org guards** (`requireOrgSession`, `getOrgTenantContext`, `requireSignedInSession`, `requireGlobalAdminSession`, …) from here.
- **Forbidden:** `#lib/tenant` and `lib/tenant.ts` — session/org guards live in `lib/auth/tenant-session.server.ts` and are exported from `#lib/auth`. See **AGENTS.md §6.1–6.3**.
- **Do not** deep-import `lib/auth/neon.server.ts` from `app/` or ERP features. **Exception:** low-level `lib` modules that load the Neon instance before the barrel (e.g. [`lib/session-cache.ts`](lib/session-cache.ts)) may use `#lib/auth/neon.server` only.
- **Shared helpers** (Edge/client-safe, no React, no `server-only`):
  - `#lib/auth/callback-path` — post-auth URL validation
  - `lib/auth/forwarded-path-headers.shared.ts` — proxy-safe header names (`proxy.ts` must not import `server-only` / `next/headers`)
  - `lib/auth/auth-status.shared.ts` — canonical interruption codes (`authStatus` query param)
  - `lib/auth/auth-interruption-url.shared.ts` — bookmarkable interruption URLs (requires `locale: AppLocale`)
  - `lib/auth/auth-client-error.shared.ts` — `normalizeAuthClientError`, `AUTH_CLIENT_ERROR_CODE` (client sign-in error normalization; not for server interruption URLs)
  - `lib/auth/auth-status-copy.ts` — UI copy resolver
  - `#lib/auth/org-slug.shared` — `normalizeOrgSlugParam`, `ORG_SLUG_MAX_LENGTH` (URL `[orgSlug]` validation)
  - `#lib/auth/org-slug-generate.shared` — `slugifyOrganizationName`, `isReservedOrgSlug`, `RESERVED_ORG_SLUGS`
  - `#lib/auth/org-membership.shared` — `mapIamSessionUser`, IAM session user field types
- **Server-only helpers** (deep import or `#lib/auth` barrel):
  - `#lib/auth/tenant-session.server` — `requireOrgSession`, `getOrgTenantContext`, `requireSignedInSession`, `setActiveOrganizationForSession`, `getOrgSessionFromRequest`, **`getOrgSessionFromRequestTrusted`** (route handlers; DB-backed `activeOrganizationId` — see E2E playbook) (also re-exported from `#lib/auth`)
  - `#lib/auth/org-membership.server` — `hasOrgMembership`, `assertOrgMembership`, `findOrganizationIdBySlug` (membership truth used by tenant + auth-shell guards)
  - `#lib/auth/org-membership.shared` — `mapIamSessionUser`, session user field types (pure; no DB)
  - `#lib/auth/session-lifecycle-audit.shared` — auth API path → `iam.session.*` audit mapping
  - `#lib/auth/org-slug.server` — slug DB lookups + `allocateUniqueOrganizationSlug` (`server-only`)
  - `interruption-redirect.server.ts` + `intended-path.server.ts` — server redirect + path capture
  - `audit.server.ts` — `writeIamAuditEvent`, `writeIamAuditEventFromNextHeaders`
  - `iam-audit-telemetry.shared.ts` — `resolveIamAuditTelemetryEnabled` (Vercel log drain gate)
- **IAM email (deep import, not barrel):** `#lib/auth/auth-mail.server.ts` — `sendAuthEmail`, `authMailContext` (intentionally no `server-only` for test importability)

## Route Handler org session (E2E + integrations)

- **`getOrgSessionFromRequest(request)`** — reads Neon Auth session from request headers; uses signed `session_data` cookie cache when present.
- **`getOrgSessionFromRequestTrusted(request)`** — same, with `disableCookieCache: true` so **`activeOrganizationId` matches DB** (required when E2E/scripts set org via SQL without refreshing cookie cache — otherwise handlers return **401** while RSC pages work).

Use **Trusted** for machine ingest and any handler that must honor post-sign-in org activation without a full client round-trip. Pair with Playwright guidance in [`docs/testing/e2e-local-playbook.md`](../docs/testing/e2e-local-playbook.md).

## Proxy and open-redirect validation

- **`proxy.ts`** stays **narrow**: cookie presence, redirects, matcher only — no business logic, no DB, no session body validation.
- **`callbackUrl`** must be validated for open redirects (same-origin relative paths only) via [`resolvePostAuthCallbackUrl`](lib/auth/callback-path.ts) before passing to client.

## ERP modules

- Do not embed IAM workflows inside `lib/features/<module>/` beyond calling guards or `#lib/auth` APIs.

## Audit action names

- `erp.<module>.<object>.<verb>` and `org.<object>.<verb>` for ERP/org events.
- `iam.session.*` for session lifecycle hooks.
- Full canonical list: **AGENTS.md §5 → IAM audit policy (ERP)**.

## Auth/IAM route groups

Pre-login auth uses a **three-layer stack** (each layer has `_SEAL.md`):

```txt
Layer 1 — app/[locale]/(auth)/**     routes + AuthPageFrame
Layer 2 — lib/auth/                  IAM control plane (#lib/auth)
Layer 3 — components2/auth/          Card + client forms (#components2/auth/*)
```

Locale-first routes under `app/[locale]/(auth)/**` (auth flows: sign-in, sign-up, verify-email, forgot/reset password, accept-invitation) and **`app/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/iam-profile/**`** (signed-in identity + security). Legacy `/{locale}/account/*` redirects session-aware to org profile. Post-login org bootstrap lives under **`/{locale}/console`** (`app/[locale]/console/**`) — see **`docs/decisions/0003-post-login-loading-bay-nexus.md`**.
- Both route groups import **`#lib/auth`** (server) and **`#lib/auth-client`** (client) directly — no intermediary barrel.
- Auth/account shell session guards: **`requireAuthShellSignedInSession`**, **`requireAuthShellOrgSession`**, **`requireAuthShellGlobalAdminSession`** from **`#lib/auth`** (`lib/auth/auth-shell-session.server.ts`).
- Neon webhook receiver: `app/api/integrations/neon-auth-webhooks/route.ts` — verify with **`verifyNeonAuthWebhookSignature`** from **`#lib/auth`**.

## Contract changes

- New filenames under `lib/auth/` or new IAM categories require updating **`AGENTS.md`** in the same change.
